                <h3>COVID-19: Immunization continues</h3>
                <h4>12 January 2021, Ben Solo</h4>
                <p>
                    This is a daily report and updates on the COVID-19 vaccine and immunization here in Nova Scotia. 
                    <br>New Confirmed Cases: 1
                    <br>Active Cases: 27
                    <br>Patients in hospital: 0 <br>
                    “About 140,000 doses are expected by the end of March in the first phase of a three-phase immunization plan, 
                    and another million doses are expected to be delivered between April and June."<br>
                    For more information, visit the <a href="https://novascotia.ca/coronavirus/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nova Scotia Coronavirus Website</a> and <a href="https://novascotia.ca/news/search/?dept=180" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nova Scotia COVID-19 News Releases Website.</a>
